31 , 1955 ; what the book is for : how the book took shape ( a pamphlet written upon completion of the final volumes of a study of history ) and a comment written in response to the articles by edward fiess and pieter geyl ( originally published in journal of the history of ideas , vol . 16 , 1955 . )   arnold toynbee suggests that the civilisation as a whole is the proper unit for the study of history , not the nation state , which he suggests is just a part of a larger whole .

genesis : his 12-volume " a study of history " probed the genesis , growth & decline of the world 's great civilizations

